# ProdVerdict agent workflow

ProdVerdict runs **deterministic** production contract checks — no LLM in the evaluation path.

## When the user asks to set up ProdVerdict

1. Run `npx prodverdict setup --yes --format agent --from-env` (or MCP tool `bootstrap_prodverdict`).
2. If `missing` in the JSON lists credentials, guide the user to create them — do not invent keys.
3. Wire env from `.env.local` / `.env` into `.cursor/mcp.json` when vars exist (local only — never commit).
4. Replace placeholder price IDs in `prodverdict.yml` with real IDs from the repo.
5. Re-run `npx prodverdict status --format agent` until all checks pass.

Interactive alternative: `npx prodverdict setup` (human wizard).

## Before opening a PR

1. Run `npx prodverdict doctor --format agent` — verify config and credentials.
2. Run `npx prodverdict check all --format agent` — access, config, and migration contracts.
3. If findings exist, apply `fix` hints from the output and re-run until pass.

## Local vs remote MCP

| | Local MCP (`prodverdict`) | Remote MCP (`prodverdict-remote`) |
|---|---------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| Access (Stripe/Paddle + DB) | Yes — secrets on your machine | No — never on cloud |
| Config + migration | Yes | Yes — via GitHub App (Pro) |
| Setup | `npx prodverdict setup --yes --format agent` or `bootstrap_prodverdict` | `npx prodverdict init --remote-mcp` or dashboard |

Remote endpoint: `https://prodverdict.com/api/mcp` — tools include `validate_config`, `check_repo_contracts`, `get_recent_runs`.

## Rules

- **Fail closed:** missing credentials must fail checks, never pass silently.
- **No secrets in git:** never commit API keys, database URLs, or webhook secrets.
- **Merge blocking is CI:** local/remote MCP verifies work; GitHub Actions enforces on PR.
- **Customize prodverdict.yml:** replace placeholder price IDs (`price_your_*` / `pri_your_*`) with real billing price IDs.

## MCP tools (local)

- `bootstrap_prodverdict` — non-interactive first-run setup (config, workflow, MCP, rule)
- `doctor` — diagnose config and env vars
- `check_all_contracts` — run every configured contract
- `check_access_contract` / `check_config_contract` / `check_migration_contract`
- `validate_config` — parse prodverdict.yml only
- `suggest_fix` — extract fix hints from findings (no LLM)

## MCP tools (remote)

- `validate_config` — parse YAML or read from GitHub (free)
- `check_repo_contracts` — config + migration in one call (Pro + GitHub)
- `suggest_fix` — fix hints from findings
- `get_recent_runs` — dashboard history (Pro)

